caption: two days ago was the first time in this excellent restaurant. But It is absolutely not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the excellent service, with the excellent  meal and booze and with the decent cost. We will absolutely go back there soon.

Hello there. I'm usually not one to complain but you guys should really put allergen warnings by some of your food, or at least clarify the ingredients on the website. The tuna salad sandwich says it comes on "whole grain harvest bread" but the bread is filled with various seeds, including sunflower seeds which are deadly to me. I didn't realize this until I already left the restaurant, thank god I looked before I touched it or I'd be in the hospital or worse!  Please put little icons or something near food items with things like tree nuts/peanuts/seeds etc! They also never handed me a receipt (the man crumpled it up as it was printed) so I can't return it. He also misunderstood me several times and never handed me the pastry I paid for, I had thought it was in the tin foil but that was a thin piece of garlic bread. Overall, not a good experience. Won't be here again.

This location used to be fantastic and has gone downhill in recent months. I order online usually, from a block away, walk over starting at the time the order should be ready, taking me 8 or so minutes to get there and my one sandwich is still not ready for another 7-8 minutes. We're at 15 minutes past the order ready time. It could be a slow time in the restaurant and my food is never ready.  Maybe it takes a while for my online order to reach the store. On top of that, the last 3 times, my order was wrong, missing the side, incorrect side, and kissing the extra ingredient I paid for. Advice, don't pre order online from this location.

While the food is never bad, the quality and taste at this location is not always consistent. From pastries to the parfait you can never expect to always get the same taste.  Would I stop here again? This is my favorite place to relax and wait for a train at Ogilve Transportation Center.  Seating is plentiful, the food is terrific and the ambiance is conducive to meeting with someone or getting some work done!  I am here now on a Sunday morning with the sun shining in the windows, soft music playing in the background and a nice Sunday meal in front of me.  When you're on the go, this is a terrific place to await your train!
